# DEFINATION:

It is used to filter out valuesin the collection for which the condition is "false",
it gives the results for only true case

# SYNTAX:

filter(function_name,iterable)


FOR EXAMPLE: Define a function to check if a given number is even or odd.
Create a list of numbers.
Fetch only even number from the number

CODE:

  def even_odd(x):
  if x%2==0:
  return x
  
  l=[13,10,12,18,19,15]
  list(filter(even_Odd,l))
  
  
  OUTPUT:
  (10,12,18)  [BECAUSE EVEN CONDITION WAS GIVEN SO WE GOT THESE OUTPUTS]
